27/02/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- Four Greeks and one Turkish national died in a bus accident in western Turkey on Friday (February 25th), authorities announced.
Five others were injured.
The accident happened when the bus -- bound from Athens -- skidded off a road and overturned amid bad weather conditions near the town of Malkara.
That's about 200km west of Istanbul, where the tourists were headed.
(ANA-MPA, Hurriyet, Dogan - 25/02/11)
